          ]
        }
      ],
      "instructions": [
        "Preheat oven to 350°F.",
        "In a bowl, mix together the breadcrumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, garlic, and 1/4 cup of the olive oil.",
        "Season each slice of beef with salt and pepper. Divide the breadcrumb mixture evenly among the slices, spreading it out in a thin layer.",
        "Roll up each slice of beef tightly and secure with kitchen twine or toothpicks. Season the outside of the rolls with more salt and pepper.",
        "Heat the remaining 1/4 cup of olive oil in a large oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat. Add the beef rolls and cook until browned on all sides, about 5-6 minutes.",
        "Add the tomato sauce to the skillet and bring to a simmer. Cover the skillet with a lid or aluminum foil and transfer to the preheated oven.",
        "Bake for 1 hour, or until the beef is cooked through and tender.",
        "Remove the skillet from the oven and let the beef rest for a few minutes before slicing.",
        "Serve the beef braciole with the tomato sauce spooned over the top.",
        "If you don't have an oven-safe skillet, you can transfer the beef rolls to a baking dish before baking in the oven. Simply brown the beef rolls in a regular skillet as directed in the recipe, then transfer them to a baking dish. Pour the tomato sauce over the beef rolls, cover the dish with aluminum foil, and bake in the preheated oven as directed. A 9x13 inch baking dish should work well for this recipe. Just be sure to let the dish cool for a few minutes before slicing and serving."
      ]
