      ],
      "instructions": [
        "Preheat the air fryer to 400°F.",
        "In a shallow dish, mix together the flour, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, salt, and pepper.",
        "In another shallow dish, beat the eggs.",
        "In a third shallow dish, mix together the panko breadcrumbs and grated Parmesan cheese (omit the cheese if using Italian breadcrumbs).",
        "Dip each chicken tenderloin into the flour mixture, shaking off any excess, then dip into the beaten eggs, and then coat with the breadcrumb mixture.",
        "Place the chicken tenderloins in the air fryer basket, making sure they don't touch.",
        "Spray the chicken tenderloins with cooking spray.",
        "Air fry for 8-10 minutes or until the internal temperature reaches 165°F and the chicken is golden brown and crispy.",
        "Serve hot with your favorite dipping sauce, such as honey mustard or ranch."
      ]
