              "scalable": false,
              "optional": true
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "instructions": [
        "In a large pot or Dutch oven, brown the beef stew meat over medium heat until it is well-seared on all sides. Remove the meat from the pot and set it aside.",
        "In the same pot, add the diced onion and minced garlic. Sauté for about 5 minutes until the onion becomes translucent.",
        "Return the browned beef stew meat to the pot with the onions and garlic. Add the carrots, potatoes, celery, frozen peas, beef broth, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, dried thyme, dried rosemary, bay leaf, salt, and pepper. Stir well to combine all the ingredients.",
        "Bring the stew to a simmer, then reduce the heat to low and let it cook for about 1.5 to 2 hours, covered, stirring occasionally. This will allow the flavors to develop, and the beef and vegetables to become tender.",
        "If you prefer a thicker stew, you can create a slurry by mixing 2 tablespoons of flour with a small amount of water until smooth. Stir the slurry into the stew and cook for an additional 10 minutes to thicken.",
        "Tikka Masala",
        "Ingredients:",
        "For the Chicken Tikka:",
        "1 ¼ lbs boneless chicken, cut into bite-sized pieces",
        "1 cup plain yogurt",
        "1 tablespoon lemon juice",
        "2 teaspoons cumin",
        "1 teaspoon cinnamon",
        "1 teaspoon cayenne pepper",
        "1 teaspoon black pepper",
        "1 teaspoon salt",
        "1 tablespoon minced fresh ginger",
        "2 garlic cloves, minced",
        "For the Masala Sauce:",
        "2 tablespoons vegetable oil",
        "1 large onion, diced",
        "2 garlic cloves, minced",
        "1 tablespoon minced fresh ginger",
        "2 teaspoons cumin",
        "2 teaspoons paprika",
        "1 teaspoon turmeric",
        "1 teaspoon coriander",
        "1 can (14 oz) tomato puree",
        "1 cup heavy cream",
        "Salt to taste",
        "For Serving:",
        "Fresh cilantro, chopped",
        "Cooked basmati rice",
        "Instructions:",
        "Marinate the Chicken: Combine the yogurt, lemon juice, cumin, cinnamon, cayenne, black pepper, salt, ginger, and garlic in a bowl. Add the chicken and mix until well coated. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, or overnight if possible.",
        "Grill the Chicken: Preheat your grill or broiler. Cook the chicken until it's just cooked through and has some charred spots, about 5 minutes on each side. Set aside.",
        "Make the Sauce: Heat the oil in a large pan over medium heat. Add the onion and cook until it's soft and beginning to brown, about 5 minutes. Add the garlic, ginger, cumin, paprika, turmeric, and coriander. Stir and cook for another 2 minutes.",
        "Add the tomato puree to the pan, stir, and simmer for 10 minutes. Add the cream and the grilled chicken. Stir well, cover, and simmer for another 10-15 minutes.",
        "Serve: Season the sauce with salt to taste. Serve the chicken tikka masala with basmati rice, garnishing with the fresh cilantro."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "brussels-sprouts-with-bacon-in-a-creamy-parmesan-sauce",
      "name": "Brussels sprouts with bacon in a creamy Parmesan sauce",
      "category": "Sauces & Condiments",
      "tags": [
        "Sauces & Condiments",
        "Italian"
      ],
      "ingredientGroups": [
        {
          "name": "Ingredients",
          "ingredients": [
            {
              "quantity": 1.0,
              "unit": "lb",
              "item": ". (450 g) Brussels sprouts, trimmed and halved"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 4.0,
              "unit": "",
              "item": "strips bacon, chopped"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 1.0,
              "unit": "",
              "item": "small onion, finely chopped"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 2.0,
              "unit": "cloves",
              "item": "garlic, minced"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 1.0,
              "unit": "cup",
              "item": "(240 ml) heavy cream"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 0.5,
              "unit": "cup",
              "item": "(50 g) grated Parmesan cheese"
            },
            {
              "quantity": null,
              "unit": "",
              "item": "Salt and pepper, to taste",
              "scalable": false
            },
            {
              "quantity": 0.25,
              "unit": "tsp",
              "item": "crushed red pepper flakes (optional)",
              "optional": true
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "instructions": [
        "Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).",
        "In a large skillet over medium heat, cook the chopped bacon until crispy. Remove the bacon from the skillet, leaving about 1-2 tablespoons of bacon grease in the pan. Set the cooked bacon aside.",
        "Add the Brussels sprouts to the skillet with the bacon grease, cut side down, and cook for about 5 minutes, or until they begin to brown. Flip them over and cook for another 5 minutes. Remove the Brussels sprouts from the skillet and set them aside.",
        "In the same skillet, add the chopped onion and cook for 3-4 minutes, or until softened. Add the minced garlic and cook for an additional 1-2 minutes, or until fragrant.",
        "Add the heavy cream to the skillet, and let it simmer for 2-3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in the grated Parmesan cheese and cook for another 1-2 minutes, or until the sauce has thickened. Season with salt, pepper, and crushed red pepper flakes (if using).",
        "Add the cooked Brussels sprouts and bacon back to the skillet, stirring to coat them with the creamy Parmesan sauce.",
        "Transfer the mixture to a baking dish and bake for 10-15 minutes, or until the Brussels sprouts are tender and the sauce is bubbly.",
        "Remove the dish from the oven and let it rest for a few minutes before serving. Enjoy your Brussels sprouts with bacon in a creamy Parmesan sauce!",
        "You can also add some breadcrumbs on top before baking for a crispy texture or serve this dish with grilled chicken or steak for a complete meal."
      ]
    },
