    {
      "id": "risotto",
      "name": "Risotto",
      "category": "Side Dishes",
      "tags": [
        "Side Dishes",
        "Italian"
      ],
      "ingredientGroups": [
        {
          "name": "Ingredients",
          "ingredients": [
            {
              "quantity": 1.5,
              "unit": "cups",
              "item": "Arborio rice (or other short-grain rice suitable for risotto)"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 4.0,
              "unit": "cups",
              "item": "vegetable or chicken broth"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 1.0,
              "unit": "",
              "item": "small onion, finely chopped"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 2.0,
              "unit": "cloves",
              "item": "garlic, minced"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 0.5,
              "unit": "cup",
              "item": "dry white wine"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 2.0,
              "unit": "tablespoons",
              "item": "butter"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 0.5,
              "unit": "cup",
              "item": "grated Parmesan cheese"
            },
            {
              "quantity": null,
              "unit": "",
              "item": "Salt and pepper, to taste",
              "scalable": false
            },
            {
              "quantity": null,
              "unit": "",
              "item": "Fresh herbs, such as parsley or basil, for garnish (optional)",
              "scalable": false,
              "optional": true
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "instructions": [
        "In a saucepan, heat the vegetable or chicken broth over medium-low heat. Keep it simmering while you prepare the risotto.",
        "In a large, wide-bottomed pan or Dutch oven, melt the butter over medium heat. Add the chopped onion and minced garlic and sauté until they become translucent and fragrant, about 2-3 minutes.",
        "Add the Arborio rice to the pan and stir it around to coat it with the butter and onions. Toast the rice for about 1-2 minutes until it becomes slightly translucent around the edges.",
        "Pour in the white wine and stir the rice constantly until the wine is absorbed.",
        "Begin adding the hot broth to the rice, one ladleful at a time. Stir the rice constantly and allow each ladle of broth to be absorbed before adding the next. Continue this process for about 20-25 minutes, until the rice is cooked al dente and has a creamy consistency.",
        "Taste the risotto and season with salt and pepper to your liking. Remember that the broth and Parmesan cheese will also add some saltiness.",
        "Stir in the grated Parmesan cheese and mix it well into the risotto until it's melted and incorporated.",
        "Remove the risotto from the heat and let it rest for a minute or two before serving.",
        "Serve the risotto hot, garnished with fresh herbs if desired."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "homemade-potato-gnocchi",
      "name": "Homemade Potato Gnocchi",
      "category": "Side Dishes",
      "tags": [
        "Side Dishes",
        "Italian"
      ],
      "ingredientGroups": [
        {
          "name": "Ingredients",
          "ingredients": [
            {
              "quantity": 2.0,
              "unit": "pounds",
              "item": "(about 4 large) russet potatoes"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 1.5,
              "unit": "cups",
              "item": "all-purpose flour, plus extra for dusting"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 1.0,
              "unit": "",
              "item": "large egg"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 1.0,
              "unit": "teaspoon",
              "item": "salt"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "instructions": [
        "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
        "Wash the potatoes and prick them with a fork a few times. Place them on a baking sheet and bake in the preheated oven for about 1 hour, or until the potatoes are tender when pierced with a fork.",
        "Remove the potatoes from the oven and let them cool for a few minutes until they are cool enough to handle.",
        "Cut each potato in half lengthwise and scoop out the flesh into a large mixing bowl. Discard the potato skins.",
        "Using a potato ricer or a fork, mash the potatoes until they are smooth and free of lumps.",
        "Create a well in the center of the mashed potatoes and add the flour, egg, and salt. Mix the ingredients together until a dough forms. It's important not to overmix the dough to avoid making it tough.",
        "Transfer the dough onto a lightly floured surface. Knead the dough gently for a minute until it comes together into a smooth ball. Be careful not to overwork the dough, as it can become tough.",
        "Divide the dough into smaller portions. Take one portion at a time and roll it into a long, thin rope, about 1/2 inch in diameter.",
        "Use a knife or bench scraper to cut the rope into small pieces, about 3/4 inch long. Repeat the process with the remaining dough.",
        "If desired, you can roll each gnocchi piece over the tines of a fork or a gnocchi board to create ridges, which can help the sauce adhere to the gnocchi.",
        "Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Drop the gnocchi into the boiling water in small batches, being careful not to overcrowd the pot. Cook the gnocchi until they rise to the surface, which usually takes about 2-3 minutes. Once they float, let them cook for an additional 30 seconds to ensure they are cooked through.",
        "Use a slotted spoon or a spider strainer to remove the cooked gnocchi from the boiling water and transfer them to a plate or a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Repeat the process with the remaining gnocchi.",
        "Serve the potato gnocchi with your favorite sauce, such as marinara, pesto, or creamy Alfredo. Toss the cooked gnocchi in the sauce of your choice and serve them hot."
      ]
    },
