    {
      "id": "french-creme-brulee",
      "name": "French crème brûlée",
      "category": "Main Course",
      "tags": [
        "Main Course"
      ],
      "ingredientGroups": [
        {
          "name": "Ingredients",
          "ingredients": [
            {
              "quantity": 2.0,
              "unit": "cups",
              "item": "heavy cream"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 0.5,
              "unit": "cup",
              "item": "granulated sugar"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 4.0,
              "unit": "",
              "item": "egg yolks"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 1.0,
              "unit": "teaspoon",
              "item": "vanilla extract"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 0.25,
              "unit": "cup",
              "item": "granulated sugar (for caramelizing)"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "instructions": [
        "Preheat your oven to 325°F (160°C). Set a large baking dish or roasting pan aside.",
        "In a medium saucepan, heat the heavy cream over medium-low heat until it begins to steam.",
        "In a mixing bowl, whisk together the egg yolks, sugar, and vanilla extract until smooth and creamy.",
        "Slowly pour the hot cream into the egg mixture while whisking constantly. Be sure to do this slowly to prevent the eggs from curdling.",
        "Once fully combined, strain the mixture through a fine mesh strainer to remove any lumps.",
        "Pour the mixture into six 4-ounce ramekins.",
        "Place the ramekins in the baking dish or roasting pan. Fill the baking dish with hot water until it reaches halfway up the sides of the ramekins.",
        "Bake for 30-35 minutes, or until the edges are set but the center still jiggles slightly when shaken.",
        "Remove the ramekins from the water bath and let them cool to room temperature.",
        "Cover each ramekin with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight.",
        "Just before serving, sprinkle about 1 tablespoon of granulated sugar evenly over the top of each custard.",
        "Use a kitchen torch to caramelize the sugar until it forms a crispy crust.",
        "Serve immediately and enjoy your delicious crème brûlée!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "tiramisu",
      "name": "Tiramisu",
      "category": "Main Course",
      "tags": [
        "Main Course"
      ],
      "ingredientGroups": [
        {
          "name": "Ingredients",
          "ingredients": [
            {
              "quantity": 6.0,
              "unit": "",
              "item": "egg yolks"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 0.75,
              "unit": "cup",
              "item": "granulated sugar"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 0.6666666666666666,
              "unit": "cup",
              "item": "milk"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 1.25,
              "unit": "cups",
              "item": "heavy cream"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 0.5,
              "unit": "teaspoon",
              "item": "vanilla extract"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 8.0,
              "unit": "ounces",
              "item": "mascarpone cheese"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 24.0,
              "unit": "",
              "item": "ladyfingers"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 1.5,
              "unit": "cups",
              "item": "strong brewed coffee, cooled"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 2.0,
              "unit": "tablespoons",
              "item": "unsweetened cocoa powder"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "instructions": [
        "In a heatproof bowl, whisk together the egg yolks and sugar until well combined.",
        "Place the bowl over a pot of simmering water, making sure the bottom of the bowl does not touch the water. Slowly whisk in the milk.",
        "Continue to whisk the mixture over the simmering water for about 8-10 minutes, or until it thickens and coats the back of a spoon.",
        "Remove the bowl from the heat and let the mixture cool for a few minutes.",
        "In a separate bowl, beat the heavy cream and vanilla extract until stiff peaks form.",
        "Gently fold the mascarpone cheese into the cooled egg yolk mixture until well combined.",
        "Gradually fold in the whipped cream, being careful not to overmix.",
        "Dip each ladyfinger into the brewed coffee, making sure to coat both sides, but not soaking them for too long as they can become mushy.",
        "Arrange a layer of soaked ladyfingers in the bottom of a rectangular or square glass dish.",
        "Spread half of the mascarpone cream mixture evenly over the ladyfingers.",
        "Repeat with another layer of soaked ladyfingers and the remaining mascarpone cream mixture.",
        "Sift the cocoa powder over the top layer of the cream.",
        "Cover the dish with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 4 hours, or overnight if possible, to allow the flavors to meld and the dessert to set.",
        "Prior to serving, dust the top with additional cocoa powder, if desired.",
        "Cut into individual portions and serve chilled."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "homemade-ladyfingers",
      "name": "Homemade Ladyfingers",
      "category": "Main Course",
      "tags": [
        "Main Course"
      ],
      "ingredientGroups": [
        {
          "name": "Ingredients",
          "ingredients": [
            {
              "quantity": 4.0,
              "unit": "",
              "item": "large eggs, separated"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 0.5,
              "unit": "cup",
              "item": "granulated sugar"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 0.5,
              "unit": "teaspoon",
              "item": "vanilla extract"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 0.5,
              "unit": "cup",
              "item": "all-purpose flour"
            },
            {
              "quantity": 0.25,
              "unit": "cup",
              "item": "cornstarch"
            },
            {
              "quantity": null,
              "unit": "",
              "item": "Powdered sugar, for dusting",
              "scalable": false
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "instructions": [
        "Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C). Line two baking sheets with parchment paper.",
        "In a large mixing bowl, beat the egg yolks and granulated sugar together until pale and thick. This can take about 3-4 minutes.",
        "Stir in the vanilla extract.",
        "In a separate bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff peaks form.",
        "Gently fold the beaten egg whites into the egg yolk mixture.",
        "In another bowl, sift together the all-purpose flour and cornstarch.",
        "Gradually fold the flour mixture into the egg mixture until well combined. Be gentle to avoid deflating the egg whites.",
        "Transfer the batter to a piping bag fitted with a round tip.",
        "Pipe the batter onto the prepared baking sheets in finger-like shapes, about 3-4 inches long and 1/2 inch wide. Leave some space between each ladyfinger.",
        "Dust the tops of the ladyfingers with powdered sugar.",
        "Bake in the preheated oven for about 12-15 minutes, or until the ladyfingers are lightly golden and firm to the touch.",
        "Remove the ladyfingers from the baking sheets and let them cool completely on a wire rack.",
        "Cannoli",
        "Ingredients: For the Cannoli Shells:",
        "2 cups all-purpose flour",
        "2 tablespoons granulated sugar",
        "1/4 teaspoon salt",
        "2 tablespoons unsalted butter, cold and cut into small pieces",
        "1/2 cup dry white wine",
        "1 egg white, lightly beaten",
        "Vegetable oil, for frying",
        "For the Ricotta Filling:",
        "2 cups ricotta cheese",
        "1/2 cup powdered sugar",
        "1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract",
        "1/4 cup mini chocolate chips (optional)",
        "Candied fruit or chopped pistachios, for garnish (optional)",
        "Instructions:",
        "In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour, granulated sugar, and salt. Add the cold butter pieces and use your fingers or a pastry cutter to cut the butter into the flour mixture until it resembles coarse crumbs.",
        "Gradually add the white wine, a little at a time, and mix until a dough forms. Knead the dough gently on a floured surface until it comes together into a smooth ball. Wrap the dough in plastic wrap and let it rest at room temperature for about 30 minutes.",
        "In the meantime, prepare the ricotta filling. In a separate bowl, combine the ricotta cheese, powdered sugar, and vanilla extract. Stir until well combined and smooth. If desired, mix in the mini chocolate chips.",
        "Heat vegetable oil in a deep fryer or large heavy-bottomed pot to about 350°F (175°C).",
        "On a floured surface, roll out the dough until it is very thin, about 1/8 inch thick. Cut the dough into circles using a round cookie cutter or a glass. The size of the circles can vary depending on your preference, but aim for around 4-5 inches in diameter.",
        "Wrap each circle of dough around a cannoli tube or a metal cannoli form, sealing the edges with a little beaten egg white.",
        "Carefully place the wrapped cannoli tubes in the hot oil, a few at a time, and fry them until golden brown and crispy, about 3-4 minutes. Use tongs or a slotted spoon to remove the fried cannoli shells and transfer them to a wire rack or paper towels to cool.",
        "Once the cannoli shells have cooled completely, gently slide the shells off the tubes.",
        "Using a piping bag or a spoon, fill each cannoli shell with the prepared ricotta filling. Start by piping the filling into one end of the shell, then fill the other end, ensuring the shell is filled completely.",
        "If desired, garnish the ends of the filled cannoli with candied fruit or chopped pistachios.",
        "Serve the cannoli immediately and enjoy!"
      ]
    },
    {
